{"metadata":{"title":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"roleHeading":"Type Method","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot6ThreadC03setC19SafetyChecksEnabledyySbFZ"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread\/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"enabled","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default, for every thread, is that they are enabled (as if called with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enabled"},{"type":"text","text":" being "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Those checks are conservative. That means that they will only succeed in considering a call thread-safe (and therefore allow it to happen) if the engine can guarantee such safety."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because of that, there may be cases where the user may want to disable them ("},{"code":"enabled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" being ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":") to make certain operations allowed again. By doing so, it becomes the user’s responsibility to ensure thread safety (e.g., by using "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"text":") for those objects that are otherwise protected by the engine.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is an advanced usage of the engine. You are advised to use it only if you know what you are doing and there is no safer way."}]}],"type":"aside"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is useful for scripts running on either arbitrary "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" objects or tasks submitted to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". It doesn’t apply to code running during "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" group processing, where the checks will be always performed."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Even in the case of having disabled the checks in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" task, there’s no need to re-enable them at the end. The engine will do so."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread\/setthreadsafetychecksenabled(_:)"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets whether the thread safety checks the engine normally performs in methods of certain classes (e.g., "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","isActive":true},{"text":") should happen ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"on the current thread"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"title":"SwiftGodot","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","abstract":[{"text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/WorkerThreadPool":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A singleton that allocates some "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread"},{"type":"text","text":"s on startup, used to offload tasks to these threads."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool","title":"WorkerThreadPool","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"WorkerThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/workerthreadpool","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"WorkerThreadPool"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Mutex":{"role":"symbol","title":"Mutex","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Mutex","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/mutex","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A binary ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Semaphore","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for synchronization of multiple "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread"},{"type":"text","text":"s."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Mutex"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Semaphore":{"role":"symbol","title":"Semaphore","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Semaphore"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Semaphore","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/semaphore","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A synchronization mechanism used to control access to a shared resource by ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"s."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Semaphore"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Thread":{"role":"symbol","title":"Thread","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Thread"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Thread","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A unit of execution in a process.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Thread/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)":{"title":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread\/setthreadsafetychecksenabled(_:)","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets whether the thread safety checks the engine normally performs in methods of certain classes (e.g., "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":") should happen ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"on the current thread","type":"text"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread\/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Node":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Node","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node","title":"Node","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Node"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Base class for all scene objects."}]}}}